    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-255@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Using kapi with Claude"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Bruke kapi med Claude"
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-256@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "You keep building with Claude Code as usual. kapi gives Claude a **structured,\nrepeatable** way to handle localization and brand — so making your product\nmultilingual and keeping its copy on-voice is an engineering pipeline, not a\none-off translation. kapi extracts the text from your **code** and\n**documents**, round-trips it back **faithfully** (structure, formatting, and\nplaceholders intact), reuses **translation memory**, and enforces your **glossary**\nand **brand voice** — the same way every time, and gate-able in CI."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Du fortsetter å bygge med Claude Code som vanlig. kapi gir Claude en\n**strukturert, repeterbar** måte å håndtere lokalisering og merkevare på — slik\nat det å gjøre produktet ditt flerspråklig og holde teksten på stemmen er en\ningeniørpipeline, ikke en engangsoversettelse. kapi trekker teksten ut av\n**koden** og **dokumentene** dine, fører den tilbake **formattro** (struktur,\nformatering og plassholdere intakt), gjenbruker **oversettelsesminne**, og\nhåndhever **ordlisten** og **merkevarestemmen** din — på samme måte hver gang,\nog kan brukes som port i CI."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-257@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "You install it once. After that you ask Claude in plain language; it decides when\nto call `kapi`."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Du installerer det én gang. Etter det spør du Claude i naturlig språk; den\navgjør når den skal kalle `kapi`."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-258@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": ":::note\nkapi also speaks [MCP](/reference/mcp), for assistants that prefer structured tools\nover a CLI. This page follows the skill (CLI) path — the two work together.\n:::"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": ":::note\nkapi snakker også [MCP](/reference/mcp), for assistenter som foretrekker\nstrukturerte verktøy fremfor en CLI. Denne siden følger ferdighetssporet (CLI) —\nde to virker sammen.\n:::"
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-259@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "1. Plug kapi into Claude"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "1. Koble kapi til Claude"
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-25@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "The bright line: **bilingual round-trip and asset interchange both hand a\nfile to a counterpart and bring the result back, with project state holding the\nway back; format conversion is one-way.** This page is the bilingual round-trip —\nthe handoff to a translator or TMS."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Den klare linjen: **tospråklig rundtur og ressursutveksling leverer begge en fil\ntil en motpart og henter resultatet tilbake, med prosjekttilstand som holder\nveien tilbake; formatkonvertering er énveis.** Denne siden er den tospråklige\nrundturen — overleveringen til en oversetter eller et TMS."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-260@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Install the skill into a project, or into your user account for every project:"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Installer ferdigheten i et prosjekt, eller i brukerkontoen din for alle\nprosjekter:"
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-261@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Claude Code discovers the skill and invokes it when a task fits its description —\nyou never call it by name. It's one router that loads the relevant section on\ndemand (progressive disclosure), so it covers the whole workflow without crowding\nthe context window."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Claude Code oppdager ferdigheten og kaller den når en oppgave passer\nbeskrivelsen dens — du kaller den aldri ved navn. Det er én ruter som laster den\nrelevante seksjonen ved behov (progressiv avsløring), så den dekker hele\narbeidsflyten uten å fylle opp kontekstvinduet."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-262@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "The only prerequisite is the `kapi` CLI on your `PATH` (`kapi version` — see\n[installation](/kapi/get-started/installation)). The rule-based checks need no\ncredential; for provider-backed translation, add one with `kapi credentials add`\n(or let the assistant translate within kapi's guardrails — more below)."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Den eneste forutsetningen er `kapi`-CLI-en på `PATH` (`kapi version` — se\n[installering](/kapi/get-started/installation)). De regelbaserte sjekkene trenger\ningen legitimasjon; for leverandørstøttet oversettelse, legg til en med\n`kapi credentials add` (eller la assistenten oversette innenfor kapis rekkverk —\nmer under)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-263@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "2. Ship your app in another language"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "2. Lever appen din på et annet språk"
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-264@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "You're taking a React or Next.js app to a new market. The English text in your JSX\nstays as it is — no message IDs, no `t(\"...\")` wrappers. You just ask:"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Du tar en React- eller Next.js-app til et nytt marked. Den engelske teksten i\nJSX-en din blir som den er — ingen meldings-ID-er, ingen `t(\"...\")`-innpakninger.\nDu bare spør:"
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-265@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "We're launching in Japan. Set up i18n with kapi-react and add a Japanese translation."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Vi lanserer i Japan. Sett opp i18n med kapi-react og legg til en japansk oversettelse."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-266@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Claude adopts the zero-wrapper [kapi-react](/react/introduction) stack and runs\na structured pipeline — the same steps every time the UI changes:"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Claude tar i bruk null-innpaknings-stabelen [kapi-react](/react/introduction) og\nkjører en strukturert pipeline — de samme stegene hver gang grensesnittet endres:"
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-267@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "The strings stay in your components as plain JSX; kapi handles the build-time\nextraction and the round-trip into a runtime dictionary, carrying placeholders like\n`{userName}` through untouched. The note *data* in your components is left alone —\nonly the UI copy is translated. Add the next locale by re-running the same pipeline."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Strengene blir i komponentene dine som ren JSX; kapi håndterer uttrekket ved\nbyggetid og rundturen inn i en kjøretidsordbok, og bærer plassholdere som\n`{userName}` urørt gjennom. Notat-*dataene* i komponentene dine får være i fred —\nbare grensesnittsteksten oversettes. Legg til neste språk ved å kjøre samme\npipeline på nytt."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-268@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "3. Translate documents, structure intact"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "3. Oversett dokumenter med strukturen intakt"
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-269@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Next, a launch one-pager — a Word document. Claude drives kapi for a structured,\nformat-faithful round-trip: kapi parses the `.docx`, translates the text, and writes\nit back with the headings, lists, bold runs, and inline fields preserved — applying\nyour glossary and translation memory along the way."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Deretter, en énsider for lanseringen — et Word-dokument. Claude driver kapi for\nen strukturert, formattro rundtur: kapi parser `.docx`-en, oversetter teksten og\nskriver den tilbake med overskrifter, lister, fete tekstløp og innebygde felter\nbevart — og anvender ordlisten og oversettelsesminnet ditt underveis."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-26@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "**Two carriers, chosen by recipient.** neokapi's native interchange format is the\nlossless **bilingual `.klz`** (`kapi extract --format klz`) — for a translator or\nreviewer working in kapi or the neokapi review tool; it carries inline codes, TM\nmatches, and term context in one file and gives integrity-verified, diffable\nreview. For a recipient on a third-party CAT tool, `kapi extract` emits **XLIFF\n2.x / PO** (the default), the industry-interop tier this page focuses on. Both go\nout and come back through the same `extract` / `merge` verbs. See\n[KLF vs XLIFF](/reference/klf/vs-xliff)."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "**To bærere, valgt etter mottaker.** neokapis egne utvekslingsformat er den\ntapsfrie **tospråklige `.klz`-en** (`kapi extract --format klz`) — for en\noversetter eller korrekturleser som arbeider i kapi eller neokapis\ngjennomgangsverktøy; den bærer inline-koder, TM-treff og termkontekst i én fil og\ngir integritetsverifisert, diff-bar gjennomgang. For en mottaker på et\ntredjeparts CAT-verktøy skriver `kapi extract` ut **XLIFF 2.x / PO** (standard),\nbransjeinterop-nivået denne siden fokuserer på. Begge går ut og kommer tilbake\ngjennom de samme verbene `extract` / `merge`. Se\n[KLF vs XLIFF](/reference/klf/vs-xliff)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-270@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Translate announcement.docx into Japanese."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Oversett announcement.docx til japansk."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-271@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Kapi CLI recipes"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Kapi CLI-oppskrifter"
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-272@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Each recipe takes a single task — estimate a job, catch UI truncation, enforce a\nglossary — states the goal, walks the steps, and lets you run the commands\nyourself. The interactive embeds run the real `kapi` binary in your browser: no\ninstall, no server, no API key. Every command shown is the command that runs."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Hver oppskrift tar én enkelt oppgave — anslå en jobb, fange opp avkutting i\ngrensesnittet, håndheve en ordliste — angir målet, går gjennom stegene og lar deg\nkjøre kommandoene selv. De interaktive innbyggingene kjører den ekte\n`kapi`-binærfilen i nettleseren din: ingen installasjon, ingen server, ingen\nAPI-nøkkel. Hver kommando som vises er kommandoen som kjører."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-273@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "For what kapi is and how the CLI and Kapi Desktop relate, see the\n[Kapi overview](/kapi/overview). For every command and flag, see the\n[command reference](/commands)."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "For hva kapi er og hvordan CLI-en og Kapi Desktop henger sammen, se\n[Kapi-oversikten](/kapi/overview). For hver kommando og hvert flagg, se\n[kommandoreferansen](/commands)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-274@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Ad-hoc or project?"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Ad hoc eller prosjekt?"
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-275@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "A **`.kapi` project is the recommended working model** for any repository or\ncontent set you localize repeatedly. It captures the languages, content patterns,\nand flows in a committed recipe once, adds git-style upward discovery of that\nrecipe from any subdirectory, and keeps a project-local translation memory and\ntermbase that every run reuses — so you stop repeating flags and start\naccumulating work. [Create your first project](/kapi/get-started/first-project)\nwalks the setup; the [project file reference](/reference/project-file) covers the\nrecipe format and discovery rules."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Et **`.kapi`-prosjekt er den anbefalte arbeidsmodellen** for ethvert kodelager\neller innholdssett du lokaliserer gjentatte ganger. Det fanger språkene,\ninnholdsmønstrene og flytene i en innsjekket oppskrift én gang, legger til\ngit-aktig oppdagelse av oppskriften oppover fra enhver underkatalog, og holder et\nprosjektlokalt oversettelsesminne og en termbase som hver kjøring gjenbruker —\nslik at du slutter å gjenta flagg og begynner å bygge opp arbeid.\n[Opprett ditt første prosjekt](/kapi/get-started/first-project) går gjennom\noppsettet; [referansen for prosjektfiler](/reference/project-file) dekker\noppskriftsformatet og oppdagelsesreglene."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-276@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "kapi also runs **ad-hoc**: a command operates directly on the files you name,\nconfigured by flags, with nothing saved —\n`kapi ai-translate -i messages.json --target-lang fr`. That's the quick path for\none-off jobs, scripting, and CI, and a fine on-ramp. Many recipes here are shown\nad-hoc because they're genuine one-offs; each notes the project-mode equivalent\nwhere it helps."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "kapi kjører også **ad hoc**: en kommando arbeider direkte på filene du navngir,\nkonfigurert med flagg, uten at noe lagres —\n`kapi ai-translate -i messages.json --target-lang fr`. Det er den raske veien for\nengangsjobber, skripting og CI, og en fin innkjøring. Mange oppskrifter her vises\nad hoc fordi de er genuine engangstilfeller; hver av dem nevner\nprosjektmodus-ekvivalenten der det hjelper."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
          "addedAt": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
          "addedBy": "kapi tm import",
          "sessionId": "tmx-1548425fb44d29f8-1781164979411269788"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb.tmx:tu-277@tmx-1548425f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "Every recipe is marked at the top with its mode — **Runs anywhere** (ad-hoc) or\n**Needs a `.kapi` project**."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Hver oppskrift er merket øverst med modusen sin — **Kjører hvor som helst**\n(ad hoc) eller **Krever et `.kapi`-prosjekt**."
          }
        ]
      },
      "origins": [
        {
          "source": "import",
          "key": "docs-nb.tmx",
